-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription and event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscriptions_with_plans.sql
```sql
-- Join subscriptions with plans using LEFT JOIN to preserve all subscriptions
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        p.monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_users_with_companies.sql
```sql
-- Join users with companies using LEFT JOIN to preserve all users
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.name,
        u.email,
        u.company_id,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/fact/fct_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics grouped by month, tier, and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month AS month,
        sp.tier,
        uc.industry,
        sp.subscription_id,
        sp.user_id,
        b.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_with_plans') }} sp
        ON sp.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_users_with_companies') }} uc
        ON uc.user_id = sp.user_id
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
